games.bggName: Smirkle: the saracastic "sorry about that" dice game

copies.metaData:
{"VersionPublishers":"(Self-Published)","VersionLanguages":"English","VersionEmptiedInApp":0,"PublicComment":"I picked up a copy of Smirkle over the weekend and sat down to play it with some friends and family. The game was a perfect way to spend some time together and not have to think about all the turmoil in the world. I am looking forward to playing this game with my family over the holidays.

We played a few rounds and really liked the smirkle die - it added an new fun aspect to the game and we were inspired to create some new options of our own.

We bumped that bad boy up to a 12-sided die (thanks D&D) and created some additional rules to add to the 6 in the base game. Here's what we came up with:
1) Feast - Everyone gains points!
2) Famine - Everyone loses points.
3) Split - You and the player with the least (or second lowest if you have the least points) each take 4 dice and roll. You score your dice together but must each choose to roll or keep. You both gain the points you earn.
4) Steal - The points you score are taken from the player with the most points.
5) All or Nothing - You must score points on all 8 dice. If you do, gain 2000 points!.
6) Smirkle Lord - gain the smirkle lord token (we used the original d6). Redeem the token at any point between players to take an immediate bonus roll and add the total (base + points you roll) to your score. Play then proceeds as normal with whatever dice you didn't score being passed to the player to roll or they can choose to reroll all the dice.","Rating":"5","PricePaid":"","PricePaidCurrency":"","PrivateComment":"","WishlistComment":"","CurrentPrice":"","CurrentPriceCurrency":"","Barcode":"","AcquiredFrom":"","AcquisitionDate":"","InventoryDate":"","InventoryLocation":"","Quantity":"","HaveParts":"","WantParts":"","TradeCondition":""}
